Total costs and expenses for the quarter ended March 31, 2007 were $17,214,000, compared to $12,711,000 for the first quarter of 2006.   Research and development costs for the quarter ended March 31, 2007 were $13,704,000, compared to $10,511,000 for the first quarter of 2006.  Research and development costs in 2007 related primarily to expenses incurred in connection with the Company's Phase 1 trial with ARQ 197, three Phase 2 trials with ARQ 501 and the Phase 1 trial with ARQ 171.  General and administrative costs for the quarter ended March 31, 2007 were $3,510,000, compared to $2,200,000 for the first quarter of 2006.  The increased 2007 general and administrative expenses were primarily due to an increase in personnel-related expenses and facility costs previously absorbed by the Company's chemical services operations that were discontinued in 2006.
