Platform (AKIP), are focused on the identification of novel kinase inhibitors that are potent, selective and do not compete with ATP (adenosine triphosphate) for binding to the kinase.  The most advanced AKIP program is focused on the discovery of inhibitors of fibroblast growth factor receptor (FGFR).
 
