Section 8  Other Events
 
Item 8.01 Other Events.
  
On January 31, 2013, ArQule, Inc. (the Registrant) and Daiichi Sankyo Co., Ltd. (Daiichi Sankyo) announced that the first patient has been enrolled in their pivotal Phase 3 METIV-HCC clinical trial of tivantinib (ARQ 197), an investigational selective inhibitor of MET, in patients diagnosed with hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) who have received one or two prior systemic anti-cancer therapies.
As a result, the Registrant will receive a $15 million milestone payment from Daiichi Sankyo.
This payment is provided for under the terms of the license, co-development and co-commercialization agreement with Daiichi Sankyo previously disclosed by the Registrant (the Agreement).  The Agreement covers the co-development and commercialization of tivantinib by the parties in the U.S., Europe, South America and the rest of the world, excluding Japan, China (including Hong Kong), South Korea and Taiwan, where Kyowa Hakko Kirin Co., Ltd. has exclusive rights for tivantinibs development and commercialization.
Under the terms of the agreement, Daiichi Sankyo and the Registrant share the costs of development of tivantnib. The Registrants share of Phase 3 development costs are payable exclusively out of milestones and royalties received from Daiichi Sankyo under the Agreement.  Because the Registrants cumulative share of Phase 3 costs incurred but not yet paid exceeds the milestone amount, the full $15 million will be repaid to Daiichi Sankyo.
